<! [CDATA[
LATAM Chile Logo
LATAM Airlines, formerly LAN Airlines S.A. and LAN-Chile, is an airline based in Santiago, Chile, and is one of the founders of LATAM Airlines Group, Latin America’s largest airline holding company. The main hub is Comodoro Arturo Merino Benítez International Airport, with secondary hubs in El Dorado, Jorge Chávez, Mariscal Sucre, and José Joaquín de Olmedo airports. LAN Airlines was the flag carrier of Chile until its privatization in the 1990s, is the predominant airline in Chile, and Peru, and the second-largest carrier in Colombia and Ecuador, through its local subsidiaries.
